{ A fork is a double attack — one move attacks two or more enemy pieces simultaneously, forcing the opponent to lose material since they can only save one. Knights are the classic forking piece, but queens, rooks, bishops, and even pawns can fork too. Find the move that wins material by attacking two targets at once. }

{ [%csl Gf6,Gc7,Gh1][%cal Gc7g7,Gc6g6,Gf8f4,Gc8c4] }
